Cover Page.UNICEF Global database on literacy rate: Literacy rate (SDG4.6.2) – Percentage of population that can both read and write a short, simple statement about their everyday life.
UNESCO Institute for Statistics (UIS) data on literacy rate from past 2 years are used. For countries with multiple years of data, the most recent year was used.

Cover Page.UNICEF Global database on literacy rate: Three-digit alphabetical codes International Standard ISO 3166-1 assigned by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO). The latest version is available online at http://www.iso.org/iso/home/standards/country_codes.htm. (column A)
The UNICEF Global databases contain a set of 202 countries as reported on through the State of the World's Children Statistical Annex 2017 (column B)
The data source of adult and youth literacy rate is UNESCO Institute for Statistics (UIS), (column I)
Represents the year in which the data was collected. (column J)
UNICEF regions (column C) and UNICEF Sub-regions (column D)

Economies are currently divided into four income groupings: low, lower-middle, upper-middle, and high. Income is measured using gross national income (GNI) per capita, in U.S. dollars, converted from local currency using the World Bank Atlas method (column E).
